 contracted for the project, contrary to which, an alternative financier had to be found.
\par <#/>But documentary evidence available to the }{\i\fs24\lang2057 Family Mirror}{\fs24\lang2057  <-_suggest><+_suggests> that S
IDA may have reacted judiciously by withdrawing support, in view of what had been happening behind the scenes in a bid by tenderers and their accomplices in government to win the project.
\par <#/>For example, the Morogoro Regional Commissioner, Mr. Yusufu Maka
mba, had officially lobbied to the Minister for Labour, Youth and Community Development, Mr. Hassan Diria, so that he could exert pressure and use influence to have one tenderer, M/S K.S. Virdee secure the contract.
\par <#/>In a letter to the Minister on June 3, 1993 which had reference No. C.40/42/Vol. VI 42, the Morogoro Regional Commissioner told the minister that the applicant was his friend and therefore asked that he be given favour in the deal.
