\par <#/>The }{\b\v\fs24\lang2057 <&/>orth}{\fs24\lang2057  General feeling was that developed countries tended to impose terms on developing countries on what democracy implied.
\par <#/>Commonwealth Secretariat spokesperson <-/Partsy> Robertson quoted Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad as posing a cynical question: "Is it up to the donor country to decide what system is democratic and which isn't?"
\par <#/>Dr. Mohamad said it was unfair for countries in the North to judge those in the South by the standards of the former.
