\par }{\fs24\lang2057 THE Ministry of Agriculture and Livestock Development will post one expert in each village by 1992 and has taken measures to correct misallocations.
\par <#/>This was resolved here by regional agricultural and livestock officers, zonal research directors and other officials of the ministry, after their two-day conference over the weekend.
\par <#/>In one of the resolutions, the conference called on regional administrations to review their man-power positions.
\par <#/>Dar es Salaam, Tabora, Singida, Morogoro, Mbeya, Kigoma, Kilimanjaro, Rukwa, Dodoma and Ruvuma regions, which have more experts than the number of villages have been urged to reallocate the experts.
